 The stray wildebeest is said to be in the vicinity of Kranspoort, just before you descend the pass if travelling from Middelburg. At this stage it is not clear who the animal belongs to. Motorists using the route are advised to be aware of the possibility that the animal might cross the road at any time. Game farm owners in the area have been alerted.  A farm owner said that he had previously seen the wildebeest’s tracks in front of his gate, which is adjacent to where the Kranspoort pass begins to descend.     Middelburg police officer arrested during Hawks operation Botshabelo’s last song Five busted for dagga Nabbed cops granted bail  • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za 